</think> <answer> The ratio $PQ/AQ$ is $\frac{3-2\sqrt2}{1-\sqrt2}$. {{Solution|Solution}}

Let $G$ be the centroid of $\triangle BCD$. Extend $\overrightarrow{AG}$ and extend $\overrightarrow{PQ}$ to intersect at $X$. In a regular tetrahedron, the centroid and orthocenter coincide, and $\overrightarrow{AG}$ bisects $\overrightarrow{PX}$ proportionally (consider the plane perpendicular to $\overrightarrow{AG}$ passing through $G$). Construct points $G,D,H$ in the same coordinate system, but in $\triangle BCD$, where $G(0,0,0),D(0,0,1),H(1,1,1)$. Since $\overvec{AG}=\frac{1}{3}\overvec{AD}$, point $G$ has coordinates $(0,0,-\frac{1}{3})$. Point $A$ is the same in both systems, so $A(0,-1,-\frac{1}{3})$. Then the coordinates of $P$ are $(0,-\frac{2}{3},-\frac{1}{3})$, and the coordinates of $Q$ can be calculated in the coordinate system of $\triangle BCD$ by setting $z=0$ and $z=-\frac{1}{3}$. This gives points $Q_1,G,H_1$, the corresponding points of $Q,P,G,H$, respectively, in the coordinate system of $\triangle BCD$. Since $AG$ is a ray through the centroid, $P$, and $Q$, the projection of $\overrightarrow{PG}$ onto $\overrightarrow{GH_1}$ is the same as the projection of $\overrightarrow{PG}$ onto $\overrightarrow{GH}$. Finally, \begin{align*} \frac{PQ}{AQ}&=\frac{PQ_1}{AQ_1}=\frac{|\overrightarrow{PG}|\cos\angle{GH_1\overrightarrow{PG}}}{|\overrightarrow{AG}|\cos\angle{GH\overrightarrow{AG}}}=\frac{\left|\frac{\overrightarrow{PG}}{|\overrightarrow{PG}|}\cdot\frac{\overrightarrow{GH_1}}{|\overrightarrow{GH_1}|}\right|}{\left|\frac{\overrightarrow{AG}}{|\overrightarrow{AG}|}\cdot\frac{\overrightarrow{GH}}{|\overrightarrow{GH}|}\right|}\\ \ &=\frac{\left|\frac{\overrightarrow{PG}}{|\overrightarrow{PG}|}\cdot\frac{\overrightarrow{GH}+\overrightarrow{HH_1}}{|\overrightarrow{GH}+\overrightarrow{HH_1}|}\right|}{\left|\frac{\overrightarrow{AG}}{|\overrightarrow{AG}|}\cdot\frac{\overrightarrow{GH}+\overrightarrow{H_1G}}{|\overrightarrow{GH}+\overrightarrow{H_1G}|}\right|}=\frac{\left|\frac{\overrightarrow{PG}}{|\overrightarrow{PG}|}\cdot\overrightarrow{GH}\right|}{\left|\frac{\overrightarrow{AG}}{|\overrightarrow{AG}|}\cdot\overrightarrow{GH}\right|}=\left|\frac{G\left(-\frac{1}{3},-\frac{1}{3},-\frac{1}{3}\right)-G\left(0,0,-\frac{1}{3}\right)}{A\left(0,-\frac{2}{3},-\frac{1}{3}\right)-A\left(0,-1,-\frac{1}{3}\right)}\cdot H\left(1,1,1\right)\right|=\left|\frac{\left<-\frac{1}{3},-\frac{1}{3},0\right>}{\left<0,1,0\right>}\cdot H\left(1,1,1\right)\right|=\left|-1\cdot1+\left(-1\right)\cdot1+\frac23\cdot1\right|=\boxed{\frac{3-2\sqrt2}{1-\sqrt2}}.\end{align*}</answer>

